                                <li >
                                    <a href="#" id="anch_dj_dj-dj_1" class="">HIGHLIGHTS OF PRESCRIBING INFORMATION</a>
                                    
                                    <div class="toggle-content closed long-content Highlights" id="Highlights">

<div class="HighlightsDisclaimer">
<span class="Italics">These highlights do not include all the information needed to use RHINOCORT AQUA<span class="Sup">®</span> Nasal Spray safely and effectively. See full prescribing information for RHINOCORT AQUA Nasal Spray. </span>
<br/>RHINOCORT AQUA 32 mcg (budesonide) Nasal Spray.<br/>INITIAL U.S. APPROVAL: 1999</div>
<div></div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>INDICATIONS AND USAGE</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">RHINOCORT AQUA Nasal Spray is a corticosteroid indicated for:  (<a href="#section-1">1</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Treatment of seasonal or perennial allergic rhinitis in adults and children ≥ 6 years. (1.1)  (<a href="#section-1">1</a>)</p>
</div>
<div></div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">For intranasal use only.  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">Starting dosage:  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Adult and children 6 years of age and older: 64 mcg (one spray per nostril) once daily. (2)  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">Maximum dosages:  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Adults 12 years of age and older: 256 mcg (four sprays per nostril) once daily. (2)  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Pediatric patients (6 to &lt;12 years of age): 128 mcg (two sprays per nostril) once daily. (2)  (<a href="#section-2">2</a>)</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>DOSAGE FORMS AND STRENGTHS</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">Nasal Spray: 32 mcg budesonide in each metered spray. (3)  (<a href="#section-3">3</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">Supplied in 8.6 g bottle providing 120 metered sprays after initial priming. (16)  (<a href="#section-3">3</a>)</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>CONTRAINDICATIONS</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">Hypersensitivity to ingredients. (4)  (<a href="#section-4">4</a>)</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Local Nasal Effects: Epistaxis, <span class="Italics">Candida albicans</span> infections, nasal septal perforation, impaired wound healing.  Monitor patients periodically for signs of adverse effects on the nasal mucosa.  Avoid use in patients with recent nasal ulcers, nasal surgery, or nasal trauma. (5.1)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Hypersensitivity reactions:  Anaphylaxis, urticaria, rash, dermatitis, angioedema and pruritus may occur after administration of RHINOCORT AQUA Nasal Spray. (5.2)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Immunosuppression:  Potential worsening of infections (e.g., existing tuberculosis, fungal bacterial, viral, or parasitic infections; or ocular herpes simplex).  Use with caution in patients with these infections.  More serious or even  a fatal course of chickenpox or measles can occur in susceptible  patients. (5.3)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Hypercorticism and adrenal suppression: May occur with very high dosages or at the regular dose in susceptible individuals.  If such changes occur, reduce treatment with RHINOCORT AQUA Nasal Spray slowly. (5.4)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Effect on growth: Monitor growth of pediatric patients. (5.6)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Glaucoma and cataracts: Close monitoring is warranted. (5.7)  (<a href="#section-5">5</a>)</p>
</div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>ADVERSE REACTIONS</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Most common adverse reactions (incidence ≥ 2%): epistaxis, pharyngitis, bronchospasm, coughing, nasal irritation. (6.1)   (<a href="#section-6">6</a>)</p>
<p class="Highlighta">
<span class="Bold">To report SUSPECTED ADVERSE REACTIONS, contact AstraZeneca at 1–800–236–9933 or FDA at 1-800-FDA-1088 or www.fda.gov/medwatch.</span>  (<a href="#section-6">6</a>)</p>
</div>
<div></div>
<div></div>
</div>
<div class="HighlightSection">
<h1 class="Highlights">
<span>DRUG INTERACTIONS</span>
</h1>
<div>
<p class="Highlighta">·	Strong  cytochrome P450 3A4 inhibitors (e.g.,  itraconazole, etc,): Use with caution.  May cause increased systemic corticosteroid effects. (5.6, 7.1, 12.3)  (<a href="#section-7">7</a>)</p>
</div>
